'''''Star Wars Missions 19: Bounty on Bonadan''''' is the nineteenth adventure book in the ''[[Star Wars Missions]]'' young-reader series and [[roleplaying game]]. It was published by [[Scholastic]] in [[March]] [[1999]].

==Publisher's summary==
''You are a bounty hunter. The Empire has hired you to track down an Imperial engineer who has been arrested by the deadly Corporate Sector Authority security police. If you rescue the prisoner, you will be handsomely rewarded. If you don't, you will have to face the wrath of Darth Vader. Your mission: to win the bounty...and keep your life.''

''Good luck.''

==Plot summary==
The [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]], in [[Kar Lamoran]]'s ''[[Stellar Manx]]'', approach the rendezvous on [[Bonadan/Legends|Bonadan]], disguised as [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperials]]. The Imperials, in turn, are also disguised, and wait for the arrival of the transport. General [[Mordak]] meets with a [[Frap Radicon]], who assures him that Palpatine's merchandise is secure. When the transport lands, Radicon recognizes [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]], and starts a fight. [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] slips a [[Penetrator MB-450|Luxan Penetrator]] onto Radicon's person, before escaping, causing the [[Security Police/Legends|Espos]] to bear down on the Imperials. Radicon is arrested, and Mordak contacts Lord [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] at [[Fondor Shipyards/Legends|Fondor Shipyards]]. The Dark Lord, livid, dispatches a bounty hunter to Bonadan to retrieve Radicon.

The bounty hunter braves several dangers on Bonadan, including [[Swooper/Legends|swoop bikers]], Espos, and [[Anzat (species)|Anzati]]. Eventually, the hunter reaches their destination, [[Spaceport Southeast II]]. There, the hunter learns that Radicon is being held in [[Blue Level]]. The hunter rescues Radicon, and collects their reward.

Radicon then escapes, taking Lamoran's freighter to the [[Malagarr/Legends|uncharted red planet]]. The Rebels quickly learn its destination, and prepare to pursue.

